## Version Control

### Branching Strategy

- **`{{BASE_BRANCH}}`** ÔÇö primary integration branch
- **Feature branches** ÔÇö `TICKET-xxx` format, branched from `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`
- **Release branches** ÔÇö cut from `{{BASE_BRANCH}}` when ready

### Pull Request Guidelines

- **Base branch**: `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`
- **PR title format**: `{Ticket-ID}: {Story Title}`
- **Assignee**: Always assign to yourself (`--assignee @me`)

### Git Rules

- Never force push to `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`
- Stage specific files ÔÇö never `git add -A` or `git add .`
- No commits with failing tests
- Only maintainer can approve merges to `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`

## Security

- No secrets in code ÔÇö use environment variables and `.env`
- Validate all input at system boundaries
- Log operations but never log PII or credentials
- Review dependency updates for security advisories
- Keep `.env` and credential files in `.gitignore`

## Factory Mode

When invoked with `/factory TICKET-{id}`:
- All human gates use auto-defaults
- Ticket readiness checked automatically (`/check-readiness`)
- Code standards validated locally ÔÇö **deployment handled by CI**
- PR gets `factory` label Ôćĺ triggers CI workflows
- On halt: notify team, do not wait for user

### Pipeline

```
/draft-story (architect resolves questions)
    Ôćĺ /team architecture (validate design)
    Ôćĺ Ticket "Ready for Sprint"
    Ôćô
/factory TICKET-xxx
  ÔöťÔöÇ /check-readiness
  ÔöťÔöÇ Create worktree + branch
  ÔöťÔöÇ Scaffold + implement
  ÔöťÔöÇ /validate (code standards only)
  ÔööÔöÇ Commit + PR (factory label) Ôćĺ CI deploys Ôćĺ reviewer tests Ôćĺ merge Ôćĺ deploy
```

